# ── Captured Artifactory state — gitignored by default ────────────────────
# `mode: backup` writes <env>/artifactory.{yml,json} here, plus sidecars
# (system-config .xml, .apply.yml, .drift.yml). A capture contains real internal
# detail — instance hostname, LDAP manager/group DNs, user emails, the full
# system-config descriptor — so it is ignored by default; only this .gitignore
# and README.md are tracked, to keep the structure documented. To keep a
# git-tracked As-Built history, point artifactory_state_dir at a location where
# committing the captured config is acceptable.
*
!.gitignore
!README.md
